<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="334" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,654,859]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,762,787]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[462,630,762,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="33" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montegordo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[462,630,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">N. montegordo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[639,730,762,787]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[639,730,762,787]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are distinguished from those of the other species of the genus by the median septum light bulb-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[649,750,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 − 122" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1484,1507]" captionTargetBox="[213,1378,917,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[203,1384,911,1463]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 120 − 122. Neostasina montegordo sp. nov., female (120 epigyne, 121 vulva, 122 schematic course of internal duct system). b = bulge of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050786/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Fig. 120</figureCitation>
) and by the spermathecae packed into oblong sclerotized structure with irregular bulges (
<figureCitation box="[504,602,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 − 122" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1484,1507]" captionTargetBox="[213,1378,917,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[203,1384,911,1463]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 120 − 122. Neostasina montegordo sp. nov., female (120 epigyne, 121 vulva, 122 schematic course of internal duct system). b = bulge of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050786/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Fig. 121</figureCitation>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
