<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="334" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1607,2028]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,449,1607,1632]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Description. Female:</emphasis>
Prosoma orange, slightly darker along lateral margins of the cephalic region and along thoracic striae. Fovea brown. Chelicerae brown. Legs and pedipalps orange, slightly lighter than prosoma. Labium and endites orange brown, distally cream colored. Sternum orange with darker, slightly more sclerotized margins. Opisthosoma brownish gray with small, scattered yellowish brown marks on anterior half. Total length 16.7. Prosoma: 6.8 long, 6.6 wide. Opisthosoma: 5.8 long, 5.1 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.40, 0.33, 0.23, 0.32; interdistances: 0.30, 0.28, 0.57, 0.56, 0.25, 0.08. Legs (2143): I: 23.2 (6.5, 3.3, 6.1, 6.1, 1.2); II: 23.6 (6.9, 3.4, 6.1, 5.9, 1.3); III: 18.5 (5.7, 2.7, 4.4, 4.5, 1.2); IV: 22.4 (6.5, 2.5, 5.4, 6.4, 1.6). Epigyne: epigynal field rectangular, longer than wide; anterior rim entire, recurved; median septum longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1221,1859,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 − 122" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1484,1507]" captionTargetBox="[213,1378,917,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[203,1384,911,1463]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 120 − 122. Neostasina montegordo sp. nov., female (120 epigyne, 121 vulva, 122 schematic course of internal duct system). b = bulge of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050786/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Fig. 120</figureCitation>
). Vulva: glandular projections short, rounded with wide base; internal ducts indistinguishable (
<figureCitation box="[999,1159,1895,1920]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 − 122" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1484,1507]" captionTargetBox="[213,1378,917,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[203,1384,911,1463]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 120 − 122. Neostasina montegordo sp. nov., female (120 epigyne, 121 vulva, 122 schematic course of internal duct system). b = bulge of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050786/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Figs 121−122</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1607,2028]" box="[199,388,1931,1956]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1931,1956]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Male:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
