<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="335" pageId="33" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1607,2028]" box="[199,1436,2003,2028]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,2003,2028]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Remarks.</emphasis>
In this paper we describe three new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[940,999,2003,2028]" name="Cuba" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Cuba</collectingCountry>
that are known from only one sex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,416,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montegordo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,416,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Neostasina montegordo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[423,513,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,513,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[567,695,153,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turquino" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[567,695,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">N. turquino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[702,792,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[702,792,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are known solely from females and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[1200,1396,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siemprevenrde" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1200,1396,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">N. siemprevenrde</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
solely from males. Despite being found in close proximity, we believe they are indeed different species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,416,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montegordo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,416,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Neostasina montegordo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[423,513,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,513,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is significantly larger (almost twice the size) than 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[1078,1260,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siempreverde" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1078,1260,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">N. siempreverde</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1267,1356,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1267,1356,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turquino" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">N. turquino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[253,343,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[253,343,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, whereas the latter, while similar sized, show significant differences in coloration pattern.
</paragraph>
